        {
          "label": "a",
          "questionText": "Solve the inequality $\\dfrac{3x + 1}{x - 2} > 2$ where $x \\neq 2$.\nShow all your working.",
          "marks": 4,
          "commandWord": "find",
          "answerType": "inequality",
          "correctAnswer": "x < 2 or x > 5",
          "tolerance": null,
          "unit": null,
          "markScheme": [
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Multiplies by (x−2)²: (3x+1)(x−2) > 2(x−2)² oe" },
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Rearranges: 3x² − 5x − 2 > 2x² − 8x + 8 → x² + 3x − 10 > 0" },
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Factorises: (x+5)(x−2) > 0 → x < −5 or x > 2; but x ≠ 2" },
            { "mark": "A1", "desc": "Correct analysis: consider cases x > 2 and x < 2 separately to get x < 2 or x > 5" }
          ],
          "workingSteps": [
            "Case 1: x > 2 (so x − 2 > 0): multiply by (x − 2):",
            "3x + 1 > 2(x − 2) = 2x − 4",
            "x > −5 → always true when x > 2, but we need all x > 2: wait, gives x > −5",
            "With x > 2 constraint: solution is x > 2 from this case... re-examine:",
            "3x+1 > 2(x−2) → x > −5; combined with x > 2: gives x > 2",
            "Case 2: x < 2 (so x − 2 < 0): inequality flips:",
            "3x + 1 < 2(x − 2) = 2x − 4 → x < −5",
            "Final solution: x < −5 or x > 2, excluding x = 2"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
